Argued June 21, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. WILLIE STEWARD, Appellant. (No. 4975) 510 P2d 1353 Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. John H. Clough, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With bim on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osburn, Solicitor General, Salem.

affirmed June 21, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Foley and Thornton, Judges.
